  "name": "Wondrous Figurine (Obsidian Steed)",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This sinister-looking black statuette resembles a horse rearing up on its hind legs.</p>\n<p>When activated, this figurine becomes a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-bestiary.Actor.waPgKbjhijeZ00Zm]{Nightmare}.</p>\n<p>It can be called upon once per week for up to 24 hours, though it won't use <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.5bTt2CvYHPvaR7QQ]{Plane Shift}</em> or its other abilities on behalf of its rider.</p>\n<p>Although evil, it allows itself to be ridden by creatures of any alignment, although if a good creature mounts it, the rider must attempt a @Check[type:flat|dc:3]. On a failure, the nightmare uses <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.5bTt2CvYHPvaR7QQ]{Plane Shift}</em> to take the rider to a random location in the Abyss, where it promptly returns to statue form, stranding its rider in that nightmarish place.</p>"
    },
